com.vdisk.net

类 RESTUtility

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.vdisk.net.RESTUtility

  • public class RESTUtility
extends Object
    This class is mostly used internally by VDiskAPI for creating and executing REST requests to the VDisk API, and parsing responses. You probably won't have a use for it other than parseDate(String) for parsing modified times returned in metadata, or (in very rare circumstances) writing your own API calls.

      • request

        public static Object request(RESTUtility.RequestMethod method,
             String host,
             String path,
             int apiVersion,
             String[] params,
             Session session)
                      throws VDiskException
        Creates and sends a request to the VDisk API, parses the response as JSON, and returns the result.
        参数:
        method - GET or POST.
        host - the hostname to use. Should be either api server, content server, or web server.
        path - the URL path, starting with a '/'.
        apiVersion - the API version to use. This should almost always be set to VDiskAPI.VERSION.
        params - the URL params in an array, with the even numbered elements the parameter names and odd numbered elements the values, e.g. new String[] {"path", "/Public", "locale", "en"}.
        session - the Session to use for this request.
        返回:
        a parsed JSON object, typically a Map or a JSONArray.
        抛出:
        VDiskServerException - if the server responds with an error code. See the constants in VDiskServerException for the meaning of each error code.
        VDiskIOException - if any network-related error occurs.
        VDiskUnlinkedException - if the user has revoked access.
        VDiskParseException - if a malformed or unknown response was received from the server.
        VDiskException - for any other unknown errors. This is also a superclass of all other VDisk exceptions, so you may want to only catch this exception which signals that some kind of error occurred.

                                                 throws VDiskException
        Creates and sends a request to the VDisk API, and returns a VDiskAPI.RequestAndResponse containing the HttpUriRequest and HttpResponse.
        参数:
        method - GET or POST.
        host - the hostname to use. Should be either api server, content server, or web server.
        path - the URL path, starting with a '/'.
        apiVersion - the API version to use. This should almost always be set to VDiskAPI.VERSION.
        params - the URL params in an array, with the even numbered elements the parameter names and odd numbered elements the values, e.g. new String[] {"path", "/Public", "locale", "en"}.
        session - the Session to use for this request.
        返回:
        returns a VDiskAPI.RequestAndResponse containing the HttpUriRequest and HttpResponse.
        抛出:
        VDiskServerException - if the server responds with an error code. See the constants in VDiskServerException for the meaning of each error code.
        VDiskIOException - if any network-related error occurs.
        VDiskUnlinkedException - if the user has revoked access.
        VDiskException - for any other unknown errors. This is also a superclass of all other VDisk exceptions, so you may want to only catch this exception which signals that some kind of error occurred.

      • parseAsJSON

        public static Object parseAsJSON(HttpResponse response)
                          throws VDiskException
        Reads in content from an HttpResponse and parses it as JSON.
        参数:
        response - the HttpResponse.
        返回:
        a parsed JSON object, typically a Map or a JSONArray.
        抛出:
        VDiskServerException - if the server responds with an error code. See the constants in VDiskServerException for the meaning of each error code.
        VDiskIOException - if any network-related error occurs while reading in content from the HttpResponse.
        VDiskUnlinkedException - if the user has revoked access.
        VDiskParseException - if a malformed or unknown response was received from the server.
        VDiskException - for any other unknown errors. This is also a superclass of all other VDisk exceptions, so you may want to only catch this exception which signals that some kind of error occurred.

      • execute

        public static HttpResponse execute(Session session,
                   HttpUriRequest req,
                   int socketTimeoutOverrideMs)
                            throws VDiskException
        Executes an HttpUriRequest with the given Session and returns an HttpResponse.
        参数:
        session - the session to use.
        req - the request to execute.
        socketTimeoutOverrideMs - if >= 0, the socket timeout to set on this request. Does nothing if set to a negative number.
        返回:
        an HttpResponse.
        抛出:
        VDiskServerException - if the server responds with an error code. See the constants in VDiskServerException for the meaning of each error code.
        VDiskIOException - if any network-related error occurs.
        VDiskUnlinkedException - if the user has revoked access.
        VDiskException - for any other unknown errors. This is also a superclass of all other VDisk exceptions, so you may want to only catch this exception which signals that some kind of error occurred.

      • buildURL

        public static String buildURL(String host,
              int apiVersion,
              String target,
              String[] params)
        Creates a URL for a request to the VDisk API.
        参数:
        host - the VDisk host (i.e., api server, content server, or web server).
        apiVersion - the API version to use. You should almost always use VDiskAPI.VERSION for this.
        target - the target path, staring with a '/'.
        params - any URL params in an array, with the even numbered elements the parameter names and odd numbered elements the values, e.g. new String[] {"path", "/Public", "locale", "en"}.
        返回:
        a full URL for making a request.
